- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a refinement of an existing algorithm and comments on experimental results obtained by an implementation based on C++ libraries.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper mentions Krylov sequences, which are commonly used in control theory, but the context of the paper is more related to symbolic computation.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possibility as the paper deals with computing the zero set of an ideal, which can be seen as a geometric problem, but the focus of the paper is on the algorithmic techniques used to solve the problem.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possibility as the paper mentions the use of generating series expressions, which are commonly used in numerical analysis, but the context of the paper is more related to symbolic computation.
